  "text": "This clearly indicates that increase in number of plants per unit area beyond optimum level certainly reduced the amount of light availability to the individual plant, especially, to lower leaves due to shading. As the intensity of shading increases due to high population densities, the plant tends to grow taller. Such increase in height of the plant at high population densities was reported by [CITATION_1] . The increase in LAI with increase in plant density was due to more number of plants per unit area.",
